item.title: Field - fl2
item.description: Flags Map: SMF75PSD Based on: SMF75FL2 Description Flags Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description ds_accepts_vio 0 DATASET ACCEPTS VIO PAGES ds_on_alt_control_unit 2 DATASET IS ON A DEVICE WITH AN ALTERNATE CONTROL UNIT device_name_valid 3 DEVICE NAME PROVIDED IN FIELD SMF75DEV IS VALID page_space_scm 4 Page Space Type SCM

item.title: Field - fla
item.description: Flags Map: SMF75PRO Based on: SMF75FLA Description Flags Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description cnv 0 Data converted from version 2 invalid_samples 1 Invalid samples to be skipped m3r 2 Record was written by RMF Monitor III interval_smf_control 3 Interval was under SMF control lower_service_level 4 SMF record converted to lower service level. Bit is set by SMF record retrieval service GRBSMFR.

item.title: Field - flg
item.description: SYSTEM INDICATOR FLAGS Record: SMF75S1 Based on: SMF75FLG Description SYSTEM INDICATOR FLAGS Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description rrf 0 NEW RECORD FORMAT sut 1 SUBTYPES USED v4 3 MVS/ESA V4 IF ON esa 4 MVS/ESA IF ON vxa 5 MVS/XA IF ON os 6 OPERATING SYSTEM IS OS/VS2 bfy 7 SYSTEM RUNNING IN PR/SM MODE

item.title: Field - ran
item.description: Number of reassembly area. This field is used to indicate whether SMF record is broken. If 0, record is not broken. If 1, record is broken. Offset and length are only valid if SMFxxRAN is 1. Reassembly area is only present in broken records. Map: SMF75PRO Based on: SMF75RAN Description Number of reassembly area. This field is used to indicate whether SMF record is broken. If 0, record is not broken.
